edu.stanford.ramcloud

Class TableIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.ramcloud.TableIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<RAMCloudObject>

    public class TableIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<RAMCloudObject>
    This class provides the client-side interface for table enumeration; each instance of this class can be used to enumerate the objects in a single table. A new instance must be created each time the client wants to restart the enumeration.

      • next

        public RAMCloudObject next()
        Return the next object in the table. Note: each object that existed throughout the entire lifetime of the enumeration is guaranteed to be returned exactly once. Objects that are created after the enumeration starts, or that are deleted before the enumeration completes, will be returned either 0 or 1 time.
        Specified by:
        next in interface java.util.Iterator<RAMCloudObject>
        Returns:
